explanation.title: Understanding Your DISC Profile
explanation.description: The DISC assessment measures your behavioral styles across four main dimensions, helping you understand how you naturally communicate, make decisions, and interact with others.

interpretation.general: DISC assessment measures behavioral styles in four main areas: Dominance, Influence, Steadiness, and Conscientiousness.
interpretation.dominant: Your dominant profile is {{profile}}. This indicates a strong tendency to act and think according to this behavioral style.

scoring.title: How DISC Scoring Works
scoring.description: DISC assessment measures the strength of each behavioral style based on your responses.
scoring.explanation: Each response contributes to one of the four DISC styles. Your dominant style is the one with the highest score.
scoring.percentageExplanation: Your percentage shows how strongly you identify with the {{profile}} style compared to other styles.

normalityContext.D: Dominance-oriented individuals represent about 15-20% of the population. This style is common among leaders and entrepreneurs.
normalityContext.I: Influence-oriented individuals represent about 25-30% of the population. This style is common in sales and communication roles.
normalityContext.S: Steadiness-oriented individuals represent about 30-35% of the population. This style is common in supportive and helping professions.
normalityContext.C: Conscientiousness-oriented individuals represent about 20-25% of the population. This style is common in analytical and technical roles.

personalizedMessage.D: Your Dominance style means you're naturally driven to achieve results and take charge. You likely thrive in competitive environments and enjoy solving challenging problems quickly.
personalizedMessage.I: Your Influence style means you're naturally people-oriented and enthusiastic. You likely excel at building relationships and motivating others through your positive energy.
personalizedMessage.S: Your Steadiness style means you're naturally supportive and reliable. You likely create harmony in teams and provide consistent, dependable performance.
personalizedMessage.C: Your Conscientiousness style means you're naturally detail-oriented and systematic. You likely excel at ensuring quality and accuracy in everything you do.

detailedInterpretations.D: As a Dominance-oriented person, you are naturally assertive, goal-focused, and results-driven. You prefer to take control of situations and make quick decisions. You're competitive by nature and comfortable with challenges and risks. In work environments, you likely gravitate toward leadership roles and enjoy setting the pace for others.
detailedInterpretations.I: As an Influence-oriented person, you are naturally outgoing, optimistic, and people-focused. You enjoy social interaction and are skilled at building relationships. You're enthusiastic and persuasive, often inspiring others with your positive energy. You thrive in collaborative environments and enjoy variety in your work.
detailedInterpretations.S: As a Steadiness-oriented person, you are naturally patient, reliable, and supportive. You prefer stable, predictable environments and work well as part of a team. You're a good listener and helper, often putting others' needs before your own. You value harmony and prefer to avoid conflict when possible.
detailedInterpretations.C: As a Conscientiousness-oriented person, you are naturally analytical, systematic, and quality-focused. You prefer structure and clear procedures. You're detail-oriented and thorough in your approach to tasks. You value accuracy and take time to ensure things are done correctly.

D.name: Dominance (D)
D.description: You are a direct, decisive, and results-oriented person. You prefer to take control of situations and make quick decisions. You are competitive, goal-focused, and comfortable with challenges and risks.

I.name: Influence (I)
I.description: You are enthusiastic, optimistic, and people-oriented. You enjoy social interaction and are skilled at persuading and inspiring others. You thrive in collaborative environments and prefer variety in your work.

S.name: Steadiness (S)
S.description: You are patient, reliable, and supportive. You prefer stable environments and work well as part of a team. You value cooperation over competition and are naturally helpful to others.

C.name: Conscientiousness (C)
C.description: You are analytical, systematic, and quality-focused. You prefer structure and clear procedures. You are detail-oriented and take time to ensure accuracy in everything you do.

openness.title: Openness
openness.description: Measures creativity, curiosity, and openness to new experiences

openness.low: Prefer routine and traditions, being more conservative in approaches

conscientiousness.title: Conscientiousness
conscientiousness.description: Measures organization, discipline, and goal orientation
conscientiousness.low: More flexible and spontaneous, but sometimes less organized

extraversion.title: Extraversion
extraversion.high: Sociable, assertive, energetic in social interactions
extraversion.low: Prefer solitary activities and are more reserved socially

agreeableness.title: Agreeableness
agreeableness.low: More skeptical and competitive, prioritizing personal interests

neuroticism.title: Neuroticism
neuroticism.description: Measures emotional stability and stress management
neuroticism.high: More sensitive to stress and may experience emotional fluctuations
